<BaseLayout
  title="Terms & Conditions — Green Planet Gardening"
  description="Terms and conditions for Green Planet Gardening landscaping services in Cyprus. Scope of services, payment terms, cancellation policy, and governing law."
>
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-playfair text-forest mb-8">Terms & Conditions</h1>
      <p class="text-warm-gray text-sm mb-12">Last updated: 1 March 2026</p>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none prose-headings:font-playfair prose-headings:text-forest prose-p:text-charcoal/80 prose-li:text-charcoal/80">

        <h2>1. Scope of Services</h2>
        <p>M.K. Green Planet Gardening and Landscaping Ltd ("the Company", "we", "us") provides professional landscaping services in Cyprus, including but not limited to garden design, landscape construction, garden maintenance, irrigation systems, and horticultural consultation. These Terms & Conditions govern the use of our website at greenplanetgardening.eu and any services provided by the Company.</p>

        <h2>2. Quotations and Pricing</h2>
        <p>All quotations provided by Green Planet Gardening are valid for 30 days from the date of issue unless otherwise stated. Prices are quoted in Euros and are exclusive of VAT unless explicitly indicated. Final pricing may vary depending on site conditions, material availability, and scope changes agreed upon in writing between both parties.</p>

        <h2>3. Payment Terms</h2>
        <p>A deposit of 30% of the total project cost is required before work commences. Interim payments may be requested upon completion of defined project milestones. The final balance is due within 14 days of project completion. All payments should be made by bank transfer to the account details provided on the invoice. Late payments may incur interest at a rate of 1.5% per month.</p>

        <h2>4. Project Timeline</h2>
        <p>We endeavour to complete all projects within the agreed timeline. However, delays may occur due to adverse weather conditions, supply chain disruptions, or changes requested by the client. We will communicate any anticipated delays promptly and work to minimise their impact.</p>

        <h2>5. Client Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>The client is responsible for providing clear and safe access to the project site, ensuring any necessary planning permissions or approvals are obtained, and communicating any known site hazards or restrictions prior to work commencing. The client must also ensure that all underground utilities are clearly marked before excavation work begins.</p>

        <h2>6. Cancellation Policy</h2>
        <p>Cancellations made more than 14 days before the scheduled start date will receive a full refund of the deposit. Cancellations made within 14 days of the start date are subject to a cancellation fee of 50% of the deposit. Once work has commenced, cancellation will require payment for all completed work, materials ordered, and any non-recoverable costs incurred.</p>

        <h2>7. Warranty and Aftercare</h2>
        <p>Green Planet Gardening provides a 12-month warranty on all hardscaping work (stone, paving, walls, structures) against defects in workmanship. Plant material is warranted for 3 months from the date of planting, provided the client follows our care instructions. The warranty does not cover damage caused by extreme weather events, neglect, or interference by third parties.</p>

        <h2>8. Liability Limitations</h2>
        <p>Our total liability for any claim arising from our services shall not exceed the total value of the contract. We are not liable for any indirect, consequential, or incidental damages. We carry professional liability insurance and public liability insurance for all work carried out on client properties.</p>

        <h2>9. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>All garden designs, plans, drawings, and creative concepts produced by Green Planet Gardening remain the intellectual property of the Company until the project is paid in full. Upon full payment, the client receives a licence to use the designs for the specific project. Designs may not be shared with or used by third-party contractors without our written consent.</p>

        <h2>10. Force Majeure</h2>
        <p>Neither party shall be liable for failure to perform obligations due to events beyond reasonable control, including but not limited to natural disasters, government actions, epidemics, or civil unrest.</p>

        <h2>11. Dispute Resolution</h2>
        <p>In the event of a dispute, both parties agree to attempt resolution through good-faith negotiation. If a resolution cannot be reached, disputes shall be submitted to mediation before any legal proceedings are initiated.</p>

        <h2>12. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These Terms & Conditions are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Republic of Cyprus. Any legal proceedings shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Paphos, Cyprus.</p>

        <h2>13. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>We reserve the right to update these Terms & Conditions at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with the updated date. Continued use of our website or services constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.</p>

        <h2>14. Contact</h2>
        <p>For questions about these Terms & Conditions, please contact us:</p>
        <p>
          M.K. Green Planet Gardening and Landscaping Ltd<br>
          Kerynias 5, Marathounta 8520, Paphos, Cyprus<br>
          Email: hello@greenplanetgardening.eu<br>
          Phone: +357 99 245 332
        </p>
      </div>
